Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry; season all over with @bold & savory steak spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot large #pan{}. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @pear{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @spinach{5%ounce} with @creamy balsamic dressing{3%ounce} until evenly coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Add pear, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @pecans{1/2%ounce}, @croutons{2}, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup}; toss to combine.

> TIP: Add a drizzle of olive oil if salad seems dry.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide salad between #bowls{}; top salad with chicken and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.